{
  "texts": [
    "The metrics provided in ref.",
    "12 allow probing different features of generalization.",
    "There are three main pillars of generalization: (1) pre-generalization, (2) validity-based generalization, and (3) quality-based generalization.",
    "In the main text, we focus on quality-based generalization and provide details about pre-generalization and validity-based generalization in Supplementary Note 3 'Pre-generalization and validity-based generalization results'.",
    "In typical real-world applications, it is desirable to generate highquality samples that have a low cost c compared to what has been seen in the training dataset."
  ]
}